<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<br />
<p><em>Last Updated: 15-10-2024</em></p>

<p>At YouTube Channel Finder, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we collect through our service, how we use that information, and your rights regarding your data.</p>
<br />
<h3>Information We Collect</h3>
<p>Since YouTube Channel Finder does not require user registration or login, we do not collect any personally identifiable information during general use of our website. However, we may automatically collect the following types of non-personal information when you use our website:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> We may collect information about your device, such as your IP address, browser type, and operating system.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We gather information on how you interact with our website, including pages visited and features used.</li>
</ul>
<br />
<h3>YouTube API Usage</h3>
<p>Our service utilizes the YouTube API to provide you with the functionality to search for channels and content on YouTube. When you use our service, the following may occur:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Data from YouTube:</strong> We may access certain information from YouTube through the API, such as channel details and video metadata, to facilitate our service. However, this information is collected and handled in accordance with YouTube's Privacy Policy and Terms of Service.</li>
    <li><strong>API Key Security:</strong> We use a secure API key to access YouTube's services. We do not store or share your personal information with third parties through the YouTube API.</li>
</ul>
<br />
<h3>Use of Information</h3>
<p>The information we collect is used to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Provide and maintain our service.</li>
    <li>Improve user experience by analyzing usage patterns.</li>
    <li>Respond to inquiries and provide customer support (if applicable).</li>
</ul>
<br />
<h3>Contact Us Form</h3>
<p>If you choose to contact us through our <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="ContactUs">Contact Us</a> form, we may collect your email address and any other information you provide. This information will only be used to respond to your inquiries and will not be shared with third parties.</p>
<br />
<h3>Third-Party Services</h3>
<p>We do not use cookies or other tracking technologies. However, our service may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the content or privacy practices of those websites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any external sites you visit.</p>
<br />
<h3>Data Security</h3>
<p>We take reasonable measures to protect the information we collect from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
<br />
<h3>Children’s Privacy</h3>
<p>YouTube Channel Finder does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under the age of 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information.</p>
<br />
<h3>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h3>
<p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates.</p>
<br />
<h3>Contact Us</h3>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="ContactUs">Contact Us</a>.</p>
